default16
default.  
defaultThe RISJ 
defaultstudy of the way the 2007 IPCC reports were reported in the print media 
defaultaround the world showed that the media were not very good at explaining how the IPCC measured uncertainty. About 40 per cent of the articles included the IPCC concepts of likelihood and confidence levels but only 15 per cent included an explanation of what
default they actually meant 
default&#xa0;
default- such as 'very likely' meaning more than a 90 per cent probability. 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default(We are in the process of studying the 2013 
defaultIPCC 
defaultreport, so we cannot tell yet how widely these concepts were reported this time around).
